	<content type="html" xml:lang="en">
	&lt;p&gt;Over the past month I&#39;ve been working with a few people from Poland.  We are discussing how we can improve the impression of Tor in country.  It seems a few people want to make all anonymity and privacy tools illegal; and tor is a well-known scapegoat.  Thanks to the efforts of Pawe≈Ç Wilk for writing a few sane articles about online privacy and Tor in particular.  &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Sywlia Presley of Global Voices writes up a great overview of the situation at &lt;a href=&quot;http://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/01/10/poland-discussions-of-tor-and-internet-filtering/&quot; title=&quot;http://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/01/10/poland-discussions-of-tor-and-internet-filtering/&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/01/10/poland-discussions-of-tor-and-i...&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;span class=&quot;read-more&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://blog.torproject.org/blog/poland-internet-censorship-and-tor&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;read&amp;nbsp;more&amp;nbsp;&amp;raquo;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

	</content>


