<entry>
	<title>Updated guide to blogging anonymously</title>

	<id>http://localhost/jmtodaro/tor/blog/posts/Updated_guide_to_blogging_anonymously/</id>

	<link href="http://localhost/jmtodaro/tor/blog/posts/Updated_guide_to_blogging_anonymously/"/>

	<author><name>phobos</name></author>






	<category term="/tags/anonymity_advocacy" />

	<category term="/tags/anonymous_publishing" />

	<category term="/tags/global_voices" />


	<updated>2011-04-05T11:20:50Z</updated>
	<published>2009-03-13T00:58:05Z</published>

	<content type="html" xml:lang="en">
	&lt;p&gt;We worked with Sami from Global Voices to update their &lt;a href=&quot;http://advocacy.globalvoicesonline.org/projects/guide/&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;guide to blogging anonymously&lt;/a&gt;.  The big changes are more screenshots, easier instructions, and suggested use of the Tor Browser Bundle by default; as it&#39;s generaly plug and play.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The Citizen Media Law Project also has a good &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.citmedialaw.org/legal-guide/how-maintain-your-anonymity-online&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;guide to anonymity online&lt;/a&gt;.  Be sure to check out the &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.citmedialaw.org/legal-guide/potential-legal-challenges-anonymity&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;legal challenges to anonymity online&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.citmedialaw.org/legal-guide/legal-protections-anonymous-speech&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;legal protections to anonymous speech&lt;/a&gt; as well.&lt;/p&gt;

	</content>


